```{r fake-load-libraries, eval=FALSE}
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
```

```{r}
suiciderates<- read.table(here("suiciderates.csv"),sep=" ")
```

Peek at dataset:
```{r}
suiciderates
```

# Exploratory Data Analysis

How many rows?
```{r count-rows}
nrow(suiciderates)
```

How many columns?
```{r count-cols}
ncol(suiciderates)
```

Summary of suiciderates dataset:
```{r}
summary(suiciderates)
```

Out of entire dataset (27820 observations of 12 variables), what % are NAs?
```{r}
sum(is.na(suiciderates))/27820*12
```

For column HDI for year, what % are NAs?
```{r}
sum(is.na(suiciderates$HDI.for.year))/27820
```
